    <section id="myth-busters">
        <div class="container">
            <h1>Myth Busters COVID19</h1>
            <div class="myth-busters-div">
                <p><span class="myth"><strong>MYTH: </strong></span><strong>Sunlight can kill</strong> the new Coronavirus.</p>
                <p><span class="fact"><strong>FACT: </strong></span><Strong>According to WHO, there is no evidence</Strong> to prove that Sunlight kills the new Coronavirus.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="myth-busters-div">
                <p><span class="myth"><strong>MYTH: </strong></span><strong>Lemon and turmeric</strong> prevents COVID-19.</p>
                <p><span class="fact"><strong>FACT: </strong></span><strong>There's no scientific evidence</strong> that consuming lemon/turmeric can help prevent COVID-19. However, it is recommended to consume asdequate fruits and vegetables as part of a healthy diet.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="myth-busters-div">
                <p><span class="myth"><strong>MYTH: </strong></span><strong>Drinking Alcohol</strong> protects one against COVID-19!</p>
                <p><span class="fact"><strong>FACT: </strong></span><strong>Drinking Alcohol doesn't protect one from COVID-19</strong> and can be dangerous for one's health</p>
            </div>
            <div class="myth-busters-div">
                <p><span class="myth"><strong>MYTH: </strong></span>COVID-19 is an <strong>airborne disease.</strong></p>
                <p><span class="fact"><strong>FACT: </strong></span><strong>COVID-19 is NOT airborne</strong> and is mainly transmitted through droplets generated when an infected person coughs, sneezes or speaks.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="myth-busters-div">
                <p><span class="myth"><strong>MYTH: </strong></span><strong>Inhaling steam from hot water</strong> kills the Coronavirus.</p>
                <p><span class="fact"><strong>FACT: </strong></span><strong>No, inhaling steam doesn't kill the Coronavirus.</strong> Respiratory hygine, social distancing and washing hands are effective measures to prevent COVID-19.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="myth-busters-div">
                <p><span class="myth"><strong>MYTH: </strong></span><strong>Heavy intake of vitamin-C</strong> can help in curing corona infection.</p>
                <p><span class="fact"><strong>FACT: </strong></span>Regular intake of vitamin-C boosts immunity. However, <strong>excessive intake is not recommended.</strong></p>
            </div>
            <div class="myth-busters-div">
                <p><span class="myth"><strong>MYTH: </strong></span><strong>The virus survives a few hours.</strong> </p>
                <p><span class="fact"><strong>FACT: </strong></span><strong>Studies suggest that coronavirus may persist on surface for a few hours or up to several days.</strong> This may vary under different conditions. (e.g. type of surface, temperature or humidity of the environment)</p>
            </div>
            <div class="myth-busters-div">
                <p><span class="myth"><strong>MYTH: </strong></span><strong>I can COVID-19 from my pet.</strong></p>
                <p><span class="fact"><strong>FACT: </strong></span>While there has been some instance of a dog being infected, there is <strong>no evidence that a dog, cat or any pet can transmit COVID-19.</strong></p>
            </div>
        </div>
